## LLM Usage Tips

### Claude Code Best Practices
- Paste one focused prompt per session (use system token limit wisely).
- Ask follow-ups iteratively (refine pseudocode, ask for TypeScript types, request example queries).
- Copy-paste outputs into your project docs or code comments for reference.
- Build iteratively: Don't ask for all 16 prompts at once; run 2–3/week.

### SuperGrok Heavy Best Practices
- Use once (weeks 1–2) for strategic grounding.
- Reference output when making pricing/GTM decisions.
- Update mid-year with real data (beta feedback, early metrics) to refine strategy.
- Use outputs in investor pitch / business plan.

### ChatGPT Pro Best Practices
- Personas + interview guide (week 1) = foundation for all customer work.
- Landing page variants (week 2–3) = A/B test on live landing page.
- Objection handling (week 3–4) = turn into FAQ + sales script.
- Email sequences (week 7+) = implement in email service, measure conversion.

### Gemini Ultra Best Practices
- Run once (weeks 1–2), then use iteratively for blog writing.
- Keyword research → prioritize by "quick wins" (low difficulty, decent volume).
- Content calendar → stick to it; commit to 2–3 posts/month pre-launch.
- Link-building → start outreach week 4, aim for 2–3 links/month.

